		<h6>The LumoBack posture sensor is a wearable device that vibrates when a user slouches. I own the entire user experience of the product, developing the website, defining the hardware interactions, and laying out the app's user interface.</h6>
		<div id="lumo_projects">


			<div id ="strategy_mock" class="panel2 mock active">
				<div class="number">1 <small>click to expand</small></div>
				 <div class='right phone'><%= image_tag "rightarrow.png" %></div>
				<div class="words">
					<div class="title">Sensor Vibration Strategy</div>
					<div class="problem"><strong>Design Challenge<br/> </strong>Users failed to have a clear mental model of when the sensor would vibrate when in bad posture.</div>
					<div class="solution"><strong>Solution<br/> </strong>I spearheaded user interviews and guerilla usability testing, where I learned that users expect instant and constant negative feedback, along with the ability to "negotiate" with the sensor as to what is good versus bad posture. To solve for these expectations, a user can use a constant vibration within one second of falling into bad posture, or a single vibration for each new posture position.</div>
				</div>
					<div class="image image2 nonactive"></div>
			</div>
			
			<div id ="cards_mock" class="panel1 mock hidden">
				<div class="number">2 <small>click to expand</small></div>
				 <div class='left phone'><%= image_tag "leftarrow.png" %></div>
				 <div class='right phone'><%= image_tag "rightarrow.png" %></div>
				<div class="words">
					<div class="title">Insight Tiles</div>
					<div class="problem"><strong>Design Challenge<br/> </strong>A user should not be overwhelmed with data, but should be able to access important information immediately.</div>
					<div class="solution"><strong>Solution<br/> </strong>Via user interviews and think-aloud protocols with Task Rabbits, I discovered that users are most interested in single metrics delivered daily - a user very rarely compares days beyond yesterday and today. To accomodate this behavior, I designed insight tiles that reside on the lower half of the home screen. These give daily metrics with glanceable progress meters. </div>
				</div>
									<div class="image nonactive"></div>

				
			
