					<div class="title">User Defined Sensor Threshold</div>
					<div class="problem"><strong>Design Challenge<br/> </strong>A user must be able to adjust how strict the sensor is about when he or she is slouching.</div>
					<div class="solution"><strong>Solution<br/> </strong>Through a series of interactive HTML5 mocks, I discovered that this control must be posed as a question to the user, "When do you want the LumoBack sensor to buzz? When you are ...", accompanied by the avatar mimicking that amount of slouchiness. In order to control the avatar, a simple vertical slider is used.</div>
